The Sh300 million rescue cash President Uhuru Kenyatta promised to the Nzoia Sugar Company to pay farmers has not reached the company.During a talk show at a local FM station, PR manager Gilbert Awino said, &ldquo;We thank the President for giving us the Sh300 million as grant to pay farmers. However, the funds have not yet reached us. We would like them [farmers] to be patient.&rdquo;He said the funds are only for paying farmers and will not be used for any other activity.The miller owes farmers Sh263 million.